                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Bulgaria)/11–2844:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Alexander C. Kirk</persName>,
                        Political Adviser, Allied Force Headquarters, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-28T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 28, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1524. Re my 1523 of November 28, 2 p.m. General Koenig has reported that at 10:45
                    a.m. on November 25 the United States through its plenipotentiaries appended its
                    signature to the Allied protocol of November 23 [<hi rend="italic">3</hi>]
                    declaring that Bulgaria had complied with all pre-armistice requirements. The
                    ceremony took place in <pb facs="0506" n="494" xml:id="pg_494"/> Sofia in the
                    presence of British and Soviet representatives. Koenig has now returned to his
                    command at Oran.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
